rovide direction, coaching and leadership for all employees.Enforce Cinpolis values to other employees.Other duties as assigned. Qualifications Qualifications include:Strong written and oral communication along with strong analytical skills.Intermediate to Advanced understanding of functions of theater and or restaurant.Professional guest services practices.Proficient in MS Office.Ability to navigate POS.Ability to work well under pressure.Thorough knowledge of Food, Health and Safety Regulations.Flexible working hours including holidays and weekends.Requires sitting, standing, walking, lifting, twisting, bending and traversing stairs on a regular basis.Follow and enforce company policy and procedure.Maintain confidential information. BenefitsPay: DOE + quarterly bonusMedical, Dental, Vision, LifeComplimentary movie passesFood and Beverage discount</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Company Description:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Cinepolis is the world&#39;s 4th largest cinema exhibitor with 500 operations in 13 countries. Our Mission is to be the best entertainment option and continue to grow as global industry leader through fun, innovation, and stellar Guest Service.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Our US footprint began in 2011 and now has grown into a multi-unit operation in 16 cities across the nation with more to come. We seek to create a positive work culture that values hard work, collaboration, and a whole lot of fun! Come join a great team where you can make a difference and grow your career!</p><br /><br /><div style="text-align:left;padding-bottom: 20px;"><a href="/frca-apply/bk07ri" id="ApplyBottomLink" target="_blank" class="bigBlueButtonLink" rel="nofollow" onclick="javascript:setTimeout(&quot;window.location.href = &#39;/post-resume?jid=bk07ri&#39;;&quot;,1500); return true;">Go to apply&nbsp;<img src="/Images/applyarrow.png" height="21x;" width="16px;" alt="" /></a></div></div></div></div><div style="background-color: #fcfcfc; max-width: 400px